44
00:01:36.360 --> 00:01:38.320
And in particular, we're gonna be using

45
00:01:38.320 --> 00:01:41.260
what is called a rec light or a rectangle light.

46
00:01:41.260 --> 00:01:43.160
Now it's important to note that rectangle lights

47
00:01:43.160 --> 00:01:45.880
are probably the most expensive type of light

48
00:01:45.880 --> 00:01:48.000
that you can use in our scenes,

49
00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:50.100
just because of the nature of how they're built.

50
00:01:50.100 --> 00:01:52.360
And that is totally fine for what we're doing.

51
00:01:52.360 --> 00:01:53.840
For real time applications,

52
00:01:53.840 --> 00:01:55.640
I would say just be mindful

53
00:01:55.680 --> 00:01:57.640
that if you're adding a ton of rectangle lights

54
00:01:57.640 --> 00:01:58.760
into your scene,

55
00:01:58.760 --> 00:02:01.240
that's where you may notice a dip in performance.

56
00:02:01.240 --> 00:02:02.080
But again, for this scene,

57
00:02:02.080 --> 00:02:04.600
we should be totally fine to add several rec lights

58
00:02:04.600 --> 00:02:07.300
